    "1663667029efc274af": {
      "type": "collapsible-content",
      "blocks": {
        "5586f39f-c9cc-41a5-9c79-494141a820e1": {
          "type": "collapsible_tab",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "How compatible is the anymaka hammock stand? Can I use my own hammock?",
            "open": false,
            "content": "<p>The anymaka portable hammock stand works with traditional gathered-end hammocks up to 12 feet. If the hammock is excessively long, (usually due to excess rope) it can be securely fastened by wrapping the excess around the ends of the frame. If the hammock is too short, there are a couple of options available. It can be adjusted to a chair mode position, alternatively, the length of the hammock can be extended by using additional rope.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "6ca4af54-3f47-4d4d-9060-0ff238ab6d1a": {
          "type": "collapsible_tab",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Will this hammock stand fit my height?",
            "open": false,
            "content": "<p>Our hammock stand has 8 adjustable points on each arm and a 105\" / 265 cm ridgeline, and fits most people's height.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "cd3d35fb-4237-4e0c-b360-523aae405e51": {
          "type": "collapsible_tab",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "How much does it weigh? Is it really portable?",
            "open": false,
            "content": "<p>When it comes to weight, we have taken great care in designing our product to prioritize portability. It weighs approximately 10.4 kg / 23 pounds, which is comparable to carrying a small suitcase. Furthermore, our Snap-Fold design enhances its convenience by enabling effortless folding into a compact travel bag. This feature ensures that you can effortlessly carry it with you wherever you may go, without encountering any difficulties. And it's perfect for car camping or you can simply put it in the truck to enjoy ultimate relaxation.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "78977bda-88c1-4c5d-a57b-395a8e01f169": {
          "type": "collapsible_tab",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Is it solid/stable enough for outdoors?",
            "open": false,
            "content": "<p>anymaka is designed and tested above industry standards. Unlike other hammock stands made from stainless steel, anymaka stands out by utilizing aircraft-grade aluminum for the frame. This exceptional material significantly reduces weight while maintaining remarkable strength and corrosion-resistant durability. Paired with our super-durable hammock made of 40D diamond ripstop nylon fabric, it supports a weight of up to 550 lbs / 250 kg without any wobbling or touching the ground.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "6e96805a-0713-4c8f-98b5-f7f2996582ee": {
          "type": "collapsible_tab",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "How resistant is the hammock stand to rust?",
            "open": false,
            "content": "<p>The anymaka hammock stand is made of aluminum alloy, which is naturally rust-proof. Additionally, all the bolts and screws used are made of 304 stainless steel, and the stainless steel components undergo passivation treatment to enhance their corrosion resistance. The aluminum alloy used in the stand undergoes acid anodizing treatment and is coated with black textured paint to further protect it from corrosion. The product has also undergone a 36-hour salt fog test, equivalent to exposing the stand to the elements for 2 years, to ensure corrosion resistance.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "1c2b155f-fa55-47b7-b3ac-f2b66737ec17": {
          "type": "collapsible_tab",
          "disabled": true,
          "settings": {
            "heading": "How well does the canopy cover hold up against wind?",
            "open": false,
            "content": "<p>We've thoroughly tested the canopy in windy conditions during our two-year product development process. If you're dealing with a steady wind speed of 10-15 mph, with occasional gusts reaching 25-30 mph, the canopy will hold up well. It may sway a bit with the wind, but it will remain stable since it's securely fixed to the frame with bolts. However, we strongly advise against using it on the beach during high winds. Setting it up in windy conditions can be challenging, especially for beginners. We recommend assembling the canopy before attaching it to the stand. Having an extra person to assist you during setup will make the process much easier.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_tab_WQXBmY": {
          "type": "collapsible_tab",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "How should I care for my anymaka hammock stand?",
            "open": false,
            "content": "<ul><li>Never leave hammock stand unattended.</li><li>Even though it's rust-resistant, don't leave it outside when it's raining.</li><li>No need to wash the hammock stand with water. Instead, use a dry rag for cleaning.</li><li>When you're not using it, put it in the travel bag it came with and store it in a cool, dry place.</li></ul>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_tab_ytEzGe": {
          "type": "collapsible_tab",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "How should I care for my hammock?",
            "open": false,
            "content": "<p>Keep your hammock away from direct sunlight when you're not using it, and store it in a cool, dry place. When washing, take off carabiners first, use cold water and mild detergent, then let it air dry. <strong>We only recommend hand washing. </strong>If you need further cleaning, machine wash with the following instructions:</p><ul><li>Wash hammock in cold water</li><li>Do not dry clean</li><li>Do not tumble dry</li><li>Do not iron</li></ul>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_tab_re63UA": {
          "type": "collapsible_tab",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "How should I care for my canopy?",
            "open": false,
            "content": "<p>Do not launder the canopy in a washing machine. If it gets dirty, wipe it with a damp cloth or rinse it with water, then let it air dry.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        }
      },
